Package net.sourceforge.reb4j.charclass

Regular Expression Builder for Java Character Class Routines

See:
          Description

Class Summary
CharClass Base class representing an expression that matches a single character within a class of characters.
CharClass.Java Module containing predefined character classes matching character traits defined by the Character class.
CharClass.Perl Module containing Perl-style predefined character classes.
CharClass.Posix Module containing POSIX-style predefined character classes.
CharClass.Unicode Module containing predefined character classes matching a single character that has certain traits defined by the Unicode specification.
CharClass.Unicode.Letter Module containing predefined character classes matching any single character defined as a "letter" by the Unicode specification.
CharClass.Unicode.Mark Module containing predefined character classes matching any single character defined as a "mark" by the Unicode specification.
CharClass.Unicode.Number Module containing predefined character classes matching any single character defined as a "number" by the Unicode specification.
CharClass.Unicode.Other Module containing predefined character classes matching any single character that does not fit into any other category defined by the Unicode specification.
CharClass.Unicode.Punctuation Module containing predefined character classes matching any single character that is defined as "punctuation" by the Unicode specification.
CharClass.Unicode.Separator Module containing predefined character classes matching any single character defined as a "separator" by the Unicode specification.
CharClass.Unicode.Symbol Module containing predefined character classes matching any single character that is defined as a "symbol" by the Unicode specification.
CharRange Character class consisting of a range of characters.
Intersection Character class consisting of the intersection of two other character classes.
MultiChar Character class consisting of multiple characters.
NamedPredefinedClass Predefined character class that is accepted by name using \p{..} or \P{..}.
Negated<T extends CharClass> Character class representing the negation of another character class.
PredefinedClass Predefined character class referenced using an escape sequence.
SingleChar Character class consisting of a single character.
Union Character class composed of the union of two other character classes.
